&lt;p>This popular scientific book explains the science of Complexity, how it works, what anti-disciplinary science looks like and what benefits are gained by connecting different phenomena observed in traditionally distant scientific disciplines.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The book captures topics such as:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>complex networks&lt;/li>
&lt;li>synchronization&lt;/li>
&lt;li>critical phenomena&lt;/li>
&lt;li>tipping points&lt;/li>
&lt;li>the emergence of cooperation&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>and illustrates the connections between these phenomena using various examples from biology, ecology and social science.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The book is in German.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>More information, also in German is available &lt;a href="https://www.dtv.de/buch/dirk-brockmann-im-wald-vor-lauter-baeumen-28299/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&lt;strong>here&lt;/strong>&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
